<H3> <TI>   Delegation Heads for Geneva To Attend GATT Meeting 15 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1303101594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0915 GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1303101594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 13 (XINHUA) -- The 16th meeting of 
the Working Party on China of the General Agreement on Tariffs 
and Trade (GATT) is scheduled to open on March 15 in Geneva. 
  A 31-member Chinese delegation headed by Vice-Minister of 
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Gu Yongjiang and 
Vice-Minister of the State Economic and Trade Commission Yu 
Xiaosong left here in two groups on Saturday [12 March] and 
Sunday respectively for Geneva. 
  Long Yongtu, secretary general of the Chinese delegation to 
the meeting, told reporters before leaving here for Geneva that 
this meeting is the first-round negotiation on the issue since 
the end of the Uruguay Round in the end of last year. 
  During the negotiation, Gu Yongjiang and Yu Xiaosong will 
table a series of China's important measures to reform its 
foreign trade system, especially in its import system, Long said. 
  China stands for maintaining a balance of rights and 
obligations in GATT and strives to achieve positive results in 
the meeting. 
  It is learned that during its stay in Geneva, the Chinese 
delegation is expected to hold bilateral talks with the United 
States and the European Community and will also hold 
negotiations on reduction of tariffs with Japan, Canada, 
Australia and New Zealand. 

</TEXT>

