<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Hosts Sino-Japanese Economic, Trade Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1503132194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1239 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1503132194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, March 15 (XINHUA) -- The Eighth 
Sino-Japanese Economic and Trade Consultative Conference was 
held here today. 
  The regular meeting -- the series was inaugurated in 1985 -- 
focuses on economic and trade relations between the two 
countries. 
  A representative of China's State Planning Commission gave a 
brief report about the country's economic system reform and a 
representative from Japan's Ministry of International Trade and 
Industry reported on the Japanese economy. 
  Wang Zukang, director of the Shanghai Foreign Trade and 
Economic Cooperation Commission, gave a report on the city's 
foreign trade and the development of Pudong, one of China's 
largest economic development zones. 
  During the meeting, the participants from the two countries 
also discussed cooperation in machinery, hardware, light 
industry, grain and animal products. 

</TEXT>

