<H3> <TI>   Ties With S. Africa Possible After Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1603035894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0316 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1603035894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 16 (XINHUA) -- The formal diplomatic 
links between China and South Africa will be put on the agenda 
of the Chinese Government after the general election in South 
Africa to be held in April, Chinese Foreign Minister Qian Qichen 
said today. 
  But before the general election which is to elect a new 
democratic government which abandons the policy of apartheid, 
the establishment of diplomatic relations between the two 
countries is not possible, Qian told a press conference during 
the second session of the Eighth National People's Congress now 
in session. 
  China and South Africa have had links between 
non-governmental organisations, Qian said. 

</TEXT>

