<F P=100> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reports on Big Corruption Cases </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1603085194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0824 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1603085194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 16 (XINHUA) -- China's top judge and 
top procurator reported the handling of several big corruption 
cases to the ongoing session of the National People's Congress. 
  Ren Jianxin, president of the Supreme People's Court, 
reported that Li Xiaoshi, a former vice minister of the State 
Science and Technology Commission, abused his power to support a 
nationwide fraud scheme and accepted bribes of 52,000 yuan and 
embezzled 20,000 yuan, and that Li was sentenced to 20 years in 
prison on March 4. 
  Shen Taifu, general manager of the former Beijing Changcheng 
(Great Wall) Machinery and Electronics Corporation and the main 
culprit of the fraud case, was sentenced to death on the same 
day. Shen and his wife embezzled over three million yuan. 
  Both men have appealed to a higher court, he said. 
  On a cigarette smuggling case in Rushan city, Shandong 
Province, Ren said, Liu Qishan, a former head of the city 
Administration for Industry and Commerce, Fan Zhanwu, a former 
political commissar of the frontier guard sub-bureau of Weihai 
city, and Liu Ning, a section chief of the sub-bureau, were 
sentenced to death. Wang Jianzhi, former secretary of the 
Rushan municipal party committee, was sentenced to death with 
two years' reprieve. The accused have appealed to a higher 
court. 
  Zhang Siqing, procurator-general of the Supreme People's 
Procuratorate, reported several serious cases now under 
investigation. They include: 
  -- Acceptance of more than three million yuan in briberies 
by 
five bureau-level officials and 10 section-level officials in 
Minjiang Construction Bureau in Fujian Province; 
  -- Offences of embezzlement, corruption and tax evasion by 
43 
officials of the Changtu County Grain Bureau in Liaoning 
Province; 25 of them have been arrested and 32 million yuan have 
been withheld or confiscated; 
  -- Acceptance of 100,000 yuan in briberies by Guo Zhengmin, 
director of the Guizhou provincial Bureau of Public Security; 
  -- Acceptance of 20,000 yuan in briberies by Cheng Zhiwen, 
chief procurator of the Changping County Procuratorate; 
  -- Acceptance of 10,000 yuan by Li Kaipu, a chief judge in 
Hubei Province. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

