<F P=100> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Qiao Shi Holds Discussion With NPC Deputies From Shandong </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1503131794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1258 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1503131794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 15 (XINHUA) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of 
the National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, this 
morning had a talk with NPC deputies from Shandong Province 
attending the current session of the eighth NPC. 
  At the ongoing NPC session, deputies have already reached 
consensus on many major issues. What is needed to be done in 
the future is to carefully solve problems in line with the 
reality of localities and departments, he said. 
  Shandong, with a population of 80 million, is a large 
province in terms of economy. A total of 174 deputies attended 
the annual session of the NPC, of whom some are from Yimeng 
Mountains, an old revolutionary base. 
  During the liberation war period, Shandong people, 
especially 
people in the Yimeng Mountainous area contributed greatly to 
winning the war, Qiao said. 
  Today it is all the more necessary to carry forward the fine 
tradition in order to overcome difficulties and solve problems, 
he added. 
  He urged deputies to make joint efforts to do a better job 
in 
all fields. 

</TEXT>

