<F P=100> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Li Tieying Joins Zhejiang NPC Delegation Discussions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1603074494 Hangzhou Zhejiang People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1000 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1603074494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hangzhou Zhejiang People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Exclusive dispatch by reporter (Zhu Jianhua)'s from </F>
Beijing; from the "Provincial News Hookup" program] 
  [Text] On the morning of 14 March, Li Tieying, a member of 
the CPC Central Committee Political Bureau and minister in 
charge of the State Economic Restructuring Commission, arrived 
at the Labor Building -- the Zhejiang delegation's residence -- 
where he joined deputies in examining Premier Li Peng's 
government work report and discussed the great reform plan with 
them. Speaking after hearing the deputies' speeches, Li Tieying 
said: To ensure a smooth implementation of various important 
reform measures this year, we should first of all make sure that 
the system is observed, to be followed by gradual adjustment of 
interests. The two should not go simultaneously. Governments 
at various levels should meticulously organize, conduct in-depth 
studies and investigations, and continuously make adjustments. 
  Touching on Zhejiang's reform and economic development, Li 
Tieying said: Zhejiang's economic development has been quite 
unique; it depends neither on heavy state investment nor large 
Hong Kong, Macao, and foreign funds and achieves development 
with its own special economic potential, reflecting the inner 
quality of its economic development. Zhejiang is leading the 
nation in market construction, securing its leading position in 
China's markets, particularly the commodity market. Li Tieying 
expressed the hope that Zhejiang will continue to give play to 
this superiority; conduct bolder reform and exploration; develop 
intermediary service organizations; and standardize market 
construction by formulating as soon as possible trading rules, 
regulations, or interim regulations. In addition, it is 
necessary to develop markets for production factors. Government 
departments in charge of resources of production factors should 
study ways and means to standardize the production factors 
markets and gradually mature them. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

