<F P=100> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jiang Zemin Calls on Hebei Deputies </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1603052994 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1018 
GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1603052994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Feature" by XINHUA reporters Yu Shaoliang (0060 4801 5328) </F>
and Ma Kuijun (7456 7608 0689): "I'll Learn, Practice, and Work 
Together with You -- Sidelights on General Secretary Jiang 
Zemin's Meeting With Hebei Deputies"] 
  [Text] Beijing, 15 Mar (XINHUA) -- The time was 9 A.M. on 
15 March, and the place was the Hebei Hall of the Great Hall of 
the People. Hebei's 110 deputies, who were deliberating Premier 
Li Peng's "Government Work Report," were very happy when they 
learned that General Secretary Jiang Zemin was coming to see 
them. 
  At 9:10 A.M., General Secretary Jiang Zemin and Deputy Cheng 
Weigao, secretary of the Hebei Provincial Party Committee, 
entered the Hebei Hall of the Great Hall of the People chatting 
to each other. The Hebei delegation of deputies, who were 
waiting to have a group picture taken with the general secretary 
in the hall, applauded warmly in welcome. 
  General Secretary Jiang Zemin cordially shook hands and 
chatted with the Hebei deputies. The deputies extended 
greetings to him. The atmosphere in the hall was warm and 
relaxed in the few minutes before the group picture was taken. 
  After the group picture was taken with the delegation, 
General Secretary Jiang Zemin delivered an ebullient speech. He 
said: Hebei is very close to Beijing. I think I understand the 
situation in Hebei. Hebei's work was done pretty well last 
year. What I want to say is: The central authorities have 
already set major policies -- that is, Comrade Xiaoping's 
speeches made during his South China tour, the guidelines of the 
14th party congress, and the 50 points set by the Third Plenary 
Session of the party's 14th Central Committee. It is crucial to 
do a good job of implementing them. First of all, we should 
enable leading cadres at all levels to understand and grasp 
these major policies. To help people grasp the 50 points, 
relevant departments have produced a video with narratives for 
study reference. We should study while working. 
  At this point, the general secretary incidentally asked 
Deputy Ye Liansong, governor of Hebei Province: "What did you 
major in college?" "I majored in engineering," Ye Liansong 
answered. Then, the general secretary sighed with emotion and 
said: "Many of our leading comrades majored in engineering and 
technology. Now we are establishing a socialist market economy, 
and it will not work without a knowledge of economics. 
Economics is a great branch of science, but it cannot be 
grasped overnight. So we must make arduous efforts to study it 
and study it systematically." The general secretary then 
continued to say: "Capitalist countries have been engaged in 
market economies for hundreds of years, and they have indeed 
gained some experience which reflects general patterns and it 
would help us to learn. It is the first time that we have 
established a socialist market economy. So it is all the more 
necessary for us to study in practice. We have set major 
policies. We should continue to explore new ways and gain more 
experiences in practice. I place great hopes on you comrades. 
I'll learn, practice, and work together with you." 
  Immediately following the general secretary's remarks, Cheng 
Weigao said: "We will do our work conscientiously." 
  As he said farewell to the Hebei delegation, Jiang Zemin 
cordially remarked: "I hope that Hebei reaps a good grain and 
cotton harvest this year." At this, the deputies burst into 
applause. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

