<F P=100> Science &amp; Technology </F>
<H3> <TI>   Airline Orders Country's First Boeing-777 Flight Simulator </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1303162294 Beijing XINHUA in English 1410 GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1303162294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, March 13 (XINHUA) -- China Southern 
Airlines has ordered the country's first Boeing-777 flight 
simulator from abroad for training pilots. 
  The 20-million U.S. dollar contract was signed today in 
Zhuhai City, one of the country's special economic zones, in 
Guangdong Province, south China. 
  In 1992, the airlines set up a simulation training center in 
Zhuhai for Boeing pilots. With one Boeing-737 simulator and one 
Boeing-757 simulator, the center trained 716 pilots last year. 
  Pilots for Boeing previously had to go abroad for training. 
  The airline has ordered six Boeing-777s, the first of which 
is due for delivery in December this year. 

</TEXT>

